ng the council, may make suggestions to the class leader regarding potential recruits, but the class leader must work with the potential recruit to gauge his/her level of ability and officially initiate the process before recruitment will begin.<br><br>The process is as follows: <br><br>1. The class leader of a class the guild is currently recruiting finds someone whose skill level and character level meets the guild's requirement. Generally speaking, we are looking for players whose skill level is at the 90% percentile or higher.<br><br>2. The class leader or a member of the council contacts the potential recruit to see if they are interested. If the potential recruit is interested, the class leader initiates the recruitment process for a given player by officially posting so on the recruitment board.<br><br>3. A poll is created where all full guild members vote &quot;Yes&quot;, &quot;Abstain&quot; or &quot;Veto.&quot; Veto votes require a written explanation as to why and may be directly submitted to the council via email. The council will review each &quot;Veto&quot; vote and judge it valid or invalid. The poll will be up for one week and if no valid &quot;Veto&quot; votes have been cast and at least 50% have voted &quot;Yes&quot;, the member will be granted a trial membership. If there is a valid &quot;Veto&quot; vote or less than 50% voted &quot;Yes&quot; the potential recruit is informed that recruitment will not proceed further. The class leader must wait one month before re-initiating the recruitment process for a person not granted trial membership.<br><br>4. Trial membership lasts for two weeks. During this time period, the trial member is required to attend all guild raids (baring RL issues) and the guild members must attempt to group with the trial member. Raid leaders will do their best to group the trial member with various guild members to assist with this. During trial membership, a trial member has no looting rights, but does acquire DKPs which can be used if he or she becomes a full member.<br><br>5. After two weeks of trial membership another poll is created to grant full membership. This poll also lasts one week and full guild members cast &quot;Yes&quot;, &quot;No&quot; and &quot;Abstain&quot; votes. If, after one week, 90% of the votes are &quot;Yes&quot;, the trial member is granted full membership. Either the class leader of the trial member or a member of the council can individually veto the trial member at this time. If the trial member does not meet the 90% &quot;Yes&quot; requirement or is vetoed, they are informed that they will not be granted full membership and removed from the guild. The class leader must wait two months before re-initiating the recruitment process for a player previously not granted full membership.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub46.ezboard.com/uslaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slaas</A> at: 8/22/01 11:29:55 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=6.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.sacrosanctguild.com/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.threadControl?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notifica